  28. (* This function implements the Open Group specification found here:
  29.   [[1]] http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/utilities/basename.html
  30.   In step 1 of [[1]], we choose to return "." for empty input.
  31.     (for compatibility with previous versions of OCaml)
  32.   In step 2, we choose to process "//" normally.
  33.   Step 6 is not implemented: we consider that the [suffix] operand is
  34.     always absent.  Suffixes are handled by [chop_suffix] and [chop_extension].

  36. ‌let generic_basename is_dir_sep current_dir_name name =
  37.   let rec find_end n =
  38.     if n < 0 then String.sub name 0 1
  39.     else if is_dir_sep name n then find_end (n - 1)
  40.     else find_beg n (n + 1)
  41.   and find_beg n p =
  42.     if n < 0 then String.sub name 0 p
  43.     else if is_dir_sep name n then String.sub name (n + 1) (p - n - 1)
  44.     else find_beg (n - 1) p
  45.   in
  46.   if name = ""
  47.   then current_dir_name
  48.   else find_end (String.length name - 1)

  50. (* This function implements the Open Group specification found here:
  51.   [[2]] http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/utilities/dirname.html
  52.   In step 6 of [[2]], we choose to process "//" normally.
  53. *)
  54. ‌let generic_dirname is_dir_sep current_dir_name name =
  55.   let rec trailing_sep n =
  56.     if n < 0 then String.sub name 0 1
  57.     else if is_dir_sep name n then trailing_sep (n - 1)
  58.     else base n
  59.   and base n =
  60.     if n < 0 then current_dir_name
  61.     else if is_dir_sep name n then intermediate_sep n
  62.     else base (n - 1)
  63.   and intermediate_sep n =
  64.     if n < 0 then String.sub name 0 1
  65.     else if is_dir_sep name n then intermediate_sep (n - 1)
  66.     else String.sub name 0 (n + 1)
  67.   in
  68.   if name = ""
  69.   then current_dir_name
  70.   else trailing_sep (String.length name - 1)

  171.       if i = l then Buffer.add_char b '\"' else
  172.       match s.[i] with
  173.       | '\"' -> loop_bs 0 i;
  174.       | '\\' -> loop_bs 0 i;
  175.       | c    -> Buffer.add_char b c; loop (i+1);
  176.     and loop_bs n i =
  177.       if i = l then begin
  178.         Buffer.add_char b '\"';
  179.         add_bs n;
  180.       end else begin
  181.         match s.[i] with

  183.         | '\\' -> loop_bs (n+1) (i+1);
  184.         | _    -> add_bs n; loop i
  185.       end
  186.     and add_bs n = for _j = 1 to n do Buffer.add_char b '\\'; done
  187.     in

  190. (*
  191. Quoting commands for execution by cmd.exe is difficult.
  192. 1- Each argument is first quoted using the "quote" function above, to
  193.    protect it against the processing performed by the C runtime system,
  194.    then cmd.exe's special characters are escaped with '^', using
  195.    the "quote_cmd" function below.  For more details, see
  196.    https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/twistylittlepassagesallalike/2011/04/23
  197. 2- The command and the redirection files, if any, must be double-quoted
  198.    in case they contain spaces.  This quoting is interpreted by cmd.exe,
  199.    not by the C runtime system, hence the "quote" function above
  200.    cannot be used.  The two characters we don't know how to quote
  201.    inside a double-quoted cmd.exe string are double-quote and percent.
  202.    We just fail if the command name or the redirection file names
  203.    contain a double quote (not allowed in Windows file names, anyway)
  204.    or a percent.  See function "quote_cmd_filename" below.
  205. 3- The whole string passed to Sys.command is then enclosed in double
  206.    quotes, which are immediately stripped by cmd.exe.  Otherwise,
  207.    some of the double quotes from step 2 above can be misparsed.
  208.    See e.g. https://stackoverflow.com/a/9965141
  209. *)
  210. ‌  let quote_cmd s =
  211.     let b = Buffer.create (String.length s + 20) in
  212.     String.iter
  213.       (fun c ->
  214.         match c with
  215.         | '(' | ')' | '!' | '^' | '%' | '\"' | '<' | '>' | '&' | '|' ->
  216.             Buffer.add_char b '^'; Buffer.add_char b c
  217.         | _ ->
  218.             Buffer.add_char b c)
  219.       s;
  220.     Buffer.contents b
  221.   let quote_cmd_filename f =
  222.     if String.exists (function '\"' | '%' -> true | _ -> false) f then
  223.       failwith ("Filename.quote_command: bad file name " ^ f)
  224.     else if String.contains f ' ' then
  225.       String.concat "" ["\""; f; "\""]
  226.     else
  227.       f
  228.   (* Redirections in cmd.exe: see https://ss64.com/nt/syntax-redirection.html
  229.      and https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/windows/it-pro/windows-xp/bb490982(v=technet.10)
  230.   *)
  231.   let quote_command cmd ?stdin ?stdout ?stderr args =
  232.     String.concat "" [
  233.       "\"";
  234.       quote_cmd_filename cmd;
  235.       " ";
  236.       quote_cmd (String.concat " " (List.map quote args));
  237.       (match stdin  with None -> "" | Some f -> " <" ^ quote_cmd_filename f);
  238.       (match stdout with None -> "" | Some f -> " >" ^ quote_cmd_filename f);
  239.       (match stderr with None -> "" | Some f ->
  240.                                         if stderr = stdout
  241.                                         then " 2>&1"
  242.                                         else " 2>" ^ quote_cmd_filename f);
  243.       "\""
  244.     ]
  245.   let has_drive s =
  246.     let is_letter = function
  247.       | 'A' .. 'Z' | 'a' .. 'z' -> true
  248.       | _ -> false
  249.     in
  250.     String.length s >= 2 && is_letter s.[0] && s.[1] = ':'
  251. ‌  let drive_and_path s =
  252.     if has_drive s
  253.     then (String.sub s 0 2, String.sub s 2 (String.length s - 2))
  254.     else ("", s)
  255. ‌  let dirname s =
  256.     let (drive, path) = drive_and_path s in
  257.     let dir = generic_dirname is_dir_sep current_dir_name path in
  258.     drive ^ dir
  259. ‌  let basename s =
  260.     let (_drive, path) = drive_and_path s in
  261.     generic_basename is_dir_sep current_dir_name path
  262. end
